result.execSummary:
The defendant Tyler Z Steckbauer was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Manuf/Deliver Amphetamine(<=3g), a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1)(e)1.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tyler Z Steckbauer in court with attorney Andrew M. Morgan.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls 15FO167, 15CF58 and 15CF85 @ 11:54 a.m. 15FO167 - set for status conference on 12/15/15 @ 2:30 p.m. Def should appear. 15CF58 and 15CF85: Agreement stated - 15CF58 - amended information filed. Ct 2 will be dismissed and read in. Ct 1 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and other counseling as deemed appropriate, court costs. State will ask for 30 days jail, Def free to argue. Reserve right to expunge on this case only if no further crimes and successfully completes probation. 15CF85 - amend ct 1 to misd bail jumping 946.49(1)(a), plea to that and to cts 2 & 3. Ct 1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA, counseling, court costs, Ct 2 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and other counseling, cc. Ct 3 - State will argue for 5 days jail consecutive to 15CF58, State will object to expungement in this case. Atty Morgan and Def agree. Court accepts amended information on 15CF58. Plea quest. reviewed. Court grants motion to amend 15CF85 ct 1 to misd. bail jumping. 15CF58 ct 1 as amended - guilty plea. 15CF85 ct 1 as amended - guilty plea. Ct 2 - guilty plea. Ct 3 - guilty plea. Constitutional rights, elements and penalties reviewed. Atty Morgan satisfied. Court finds Def understands and pleas freely & voluntarily made. Factual basis. Court accepts pleas and finds guilty of 15CF58 ct 1 as amended and 15CF85 ct 1 misd bail jumping, ct 2 disorderly conduct, and ct 3 resisting or obstructing an officer. Ct 2 15CF58 dismissed and read in on motion of State. State heard on sentencing. Off the record 12:16. Back on the record 12:18. Arguments by Atty Morgan. Statement by Defendant. Sentencing remarks by the Court. 15CF58 - Court will follow agreement, withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, AODA and counseling deemed appropriate, may transfer to Fond du Lac Co, court costs, DNA sample but no surcharge. Def to report fingerprints on this case. Reserve right to expunge under 973.015 if successfully completes probation, pays all court obligations, no new crimes (does not include current pending charge in Fond du Lac Co.)  Review 12/6/16 @ 1:00 p.m. 20 days jail - may serve in another county as long as no electronic monitoring, huber. Report no later than 6 p.m. on 2/1/16. 15CF85 ct 1 - withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, concurrent, same conditions, court costs, DNA sample and surcharge on each ct. Ct 2 withheld sentence, 1 yr probation, concurrent, same conditions. Ct 3 - Court will order $100 plus costs instead of jail. Expungement not reserved.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. No victim rights issues. Postconviction rights. 3 days credit if revoked on 15CF85. Apply bond in 15CF85 to ct 3, pp for balance. Def advised of firearms and voting restrictions.
